Empathy Mind Map 1: Riya Patel (The Burnt-Out Developer)

Targeting the "Software Engineer" archetype with high tech comfort but daily stress.

SAYS (External Communication):

"I'll just finish this one sprint task before I take a break."

"Does anyone else feel like their head is spinning after that stand-up meeting?"

"I’m fine, just a bit of a headache from the screen glare."

THINKS (Internal Beliefs):

If I step away from my desk, my team will think I’m not working hard enough.

I can't mentally switch off; I'm still debugging code in my sleep.

I love my job, but I’m starting to hate coming into this noisy office.

DOES (Observable Behaviors):

Constantly rubs her temples and eyes while staring at code.

Skips her lunch hour to "catch up" on emails.

Wears noise-canceling headphones all day but still looks startled when interrupted.

FEELS (Emotional State):

Guilt: For needing a break in a high-pressure environment.

Overwhelm: From constant context-switching between deep work and meetings.

Exhaustion: Physical tension from screen exposure and mental burnout.

Empathy Mind Map 2: Aarav Sharma (The Anxious Manager)

Targeting the "Marketing Manager" who needs to maintain a facade of composure.

SAYS (External Communication):

"Team, let's keep it together; we have a big pitch this afternoon."

"I don't need help, I've handled bigger crises than this."

"I’ll grab another coffee; it’s going to be a long night."

THINKS (Internal Beliefs):

If I show stress, my team will lose confidence in my leadership.

My heart is racing, but I have to keep my voice steady.

I’m bringing all this tension home and snapping at my family for no reason.

DOES (Observable Behaviors):

Drinks 5+ cups of coffee a day to "fuel" through anxiety.

Checks his phone for work updates during family dinners.

Paces the hallway or taps his pen incessantly before high-stakes meetings.

FEELS (Emotional State):

Insecurity: Hidden beneath a professional "mask."

Irritability: Caused by the spillover of work stress into his personal life.

Isolation: Feeling like he has no one to talk to about his own mental health.

Empathy Mind Map 3: Priya Krishnan (The Anxious Intern)

Targeting the "New Graduate" demographic struggling with corporate adjustment.

SAYS (External Communication):

"Yes, I understand the task!" (Even when she's confused).

"I'm so happy to be here; everyone is so talented."

"Is it okay if I go to the restroom?" (Asking for permission for everything).

THINKS (Internal Beliefs):

I’m an imposter. Everyone else is so much faster and more confident than me.

I want to use the Stress Relief Pod, but I’m scared the senior staff will judge me.

I just need a place to cry or breathe for five minutes without being seen.

DOES (Observable Behaviors):

Stays late to prove her "worth," even when her tasks are done.

Over-prepares for tiny tasks due to fear of making a mistake.

Hides in her music (earbuds) during lunch because she’s too shy to network.

FEELS (Emotional State):

Alienation: Feeling like an outsider in a fast-paced corporate culture.

Fear: Of being judged or fired for showing any signs of "weakness" or stress.

Desperation: For a private, safe space to regulate her emotions.
